(60, 1, '2016-09-29 13:39:43', '2016-09-29 13:39:43', '<h1>WeatherMakers Heating, Cooling, and Plumbing Reviews and Testimonials</h1>\r\n<h2>Find Out What Our Customers Are Saying</h2>\r\nThe WeatherMakers name is known throughout Edmonton and surrounding areas for quality home heating, cooling, indoor air quality, and plumbing services. When you choose WeatherMakers, you can rest assured that you’re getting the best in quality and customer service. \r\n\r\nBeing a part of the <b>Better Business Bureau’s “55-Years of Trust” Club</b> is an assurance to you that we have remained committed to customer care and service ever since we first started serving homeowners. We will be around to take care of your family and home for years to come. \r\n\r\nWe are committed to creating long-term relationships with our clients by providing quality without compromise, and to that effect, we guarantee 100% satisfaction on all work. If you are not satisfied, we will do everything in our power to make it right. If you are still unsatisfied, we will provide you with a full refund. \r\n<h3>What Edmonton Homeowners Have to Say:</h3>\r\n<ul class="testimonials">\r\n<li>\r\n<p class="quotes"><b>Good people to work with</b>\r\nI got with Weathermakers when they gave a gold offering for coverage, and it has been very satisfactory and useful. They''ve always come out when I''ve needed them and they are always very pleasant guys. Their prices are fine; they are certainly better than everybody I had before. I''d say go for it! \r\n</p>\r\n<p class="clients">- Jan S., Edmonton</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p class="quotes"><b>Wonderful company and a great product</b>\r\nWeathermakers LTD installed an AC and Furnace for me in the early spring. The technicians that performed the installation were very professional and knowledgeable. One of the guys had been a technician for 35 years and his junior had been a technician for about 20 years.&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\nI signed a club members service contract with Weathermakers. They came out in the spring to get the AC up and running and will be out soon for the heating. Weathermakers is a wonderful company with a great product. I purchased a higher quality product from them, and it has been living up to my expectations. I would recommend their service. \r\n</p>\r\n<p class="clients">- Rob C., Edmonton</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p class="quotes"><b>Wonderful</b>\r\nIt was a pleasant experience with Weathermakers Ltd. They installed a new furnace for us. It turned out well and everything''s fine. \r\n</p>\r\n<p class="clients">- Keith C., Edmonton</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p class="quotes"><b>Prompt, helpful, and courteous</b>\r\nI have been using them for two years. They were always helpful, courteous, and prompt. They delivered on what they said. I''ve never had an issue with their product. They deliver on their promises. They also have a good value for money. Their customer service is great. I have recommended them. \r\n</p>\r\n<p class="clients">- Linda L., Edmonton</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p class="quotes"><b>Very reliable, professional, and organized company</b>\r\nI have been very satisfied with Weathermakers. They are very reliable and professional. The staff is always very courteous and respectful of customers. They have done everything for us from plumbing to air conditioning and furnace work. They know what they''re doing, and working with them for the past four years has always been a pleasant experience. I would highly recommend them. \r\n</p>\r\n<p class="clients">- Nada C., Edmonton</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p class="quotes"><b>They are there 24-7! Rapid response time!</b>\r\nI have a care package with Weathermakers. We have had them install a furnace/air conditioning, fix a water heater and take care of a few emergency type situations. The thing I like most is how quickly they respond. They have people available 24-7. It does not matter if it is 3 am or 3 pm. When our furnace went out at 2 am when it was -40 degrees o