(244, 1, '2016-10-27 16:07:41', '2016-10-27 16:07:41', '<h2>Ensure Your Electronic Equipment is Secure with Thermal Imaging Photography</h2>\r\n<p>When modern electrical equipment begins to fail, it will usually heat up before the problem manifests in more obvious ways. Thermal imaging technology makes those hot spots visible so that you can catch the problem and get it corrected before it is damaged beyond repair. This allows an electrician to safely investigate a variety of electrical equipment essential in the function and success of a business. Breaker panels, fuses, bolted connections, electrical cabinets and more can be scanned for an immediate picture of potential problems. Our master electricians have the skill and the experience to find and help solve the issue.</p>\r\n<h3>Thermal Imaging Electrical Inspections</h3>\r\n<p>Current Electrical can perform comprehensive electrical inspections on sensitive equipment components and commercial electronics. Thermal Imaging technology can help find hot spots with:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Electrical Panels</li>\r\n<li>Electrical Circuits</li>\r\n<li>Mechanical Equipment</li>\r\n<li>Heating and Cooling Equipment</li>\r\n<li>Various Electronics (Including Computers)</li>\r\n<li>Transformers</li>\r\n<li>Controllers</li>\r\n<li>Relays/Switches</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Skilled, High Tech Troubleshooting</h3>\r\n<p>Our experienced, licensed electricians can troubleshoot any commercial electrical problem you are experiencing. Continuous education and training ensures that our staff is proficient in the latest technologies – including thermal imaging inspections. A meticulous attention to detail and commitment to superior customer service drives our staff to find the solutions both quickly and efficiently. Our electricians are also committed to a clean, professional appearance; treating your business as they would their own.</p>\r\n<h4>When you need high tech troubleshooting for your commercial business, contact Current Electrical at 509-928-2522 for a variety of thermal imaging solutions.</h4>', 'Thermal Imaging', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '157-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-10-27 16:07:41', '2016-10-27 16:07:41', '', 157, 'http://ceispokane.com/157-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(245, 1, '2016-10-27 16:07:55', '2016-10-27 16:07:55', '<h2>Let Current Electric Install a Backup Generator and Never Be Without Power Again!</h2>\r\n<p>What would happen if your business lost electricity for an extended period of time? Your entire workflow would be compromised. The computer system, essential electronics, lighting, central air and general security would be eliminated. A loss of hours could be extremely detrimental to your productivity; a loss of days could affect the bottom line. Don’t let a blackout hurt your business. Installing a backup generator will help ensure your office remains productive and competitive throughout an extended power outage. Current Electrical can assist with the installation, repair and service of a commercial backup generator. </p>\r\n<h3>Emergency Insurance for Your Business</h3>\r\n<p>A commercial backup generator offers insurance in the case of a blackout. It can provide power for several days, allowing a business to continue to be productive and profitable. In areas where severe electrical storms and burnouts happen on a regular basis, it makes sense to look into a backup generator. A backup (or standby) generator restores power to your building automatically – whether or not you’re present. There’s no switch, ensuring an uninterrupted continuation of power at the proper voltage. Current Electrical can help you choose the ideal generator for your business or building needs. We’ve been keeping our Spokane neighbors connected and productive for over a decade!</p>\r\n<p>A commercial backup generator is a smart way to prevent extended power outages from affecting your bottom line. <b>The benefits of a whole house backup system include:</b></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Quick, efficient and automatic distribution of power.</li>\r\n<li>Peace of mind that essential information will not be lost. </li>\r\n<li>Uninterrupted use of electronics and heating and cooling systems.</li>\r\n<li>Maintaining office productivity and safety during blackouts.</li>\r\n<li>Protecting the electrical system from hazardous voltage fluctuations and surges when the power returns</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>When the next power outage hits your area, you’ll be glad you made the investment! Protect your business with a commercial backup generator from Current Electrical. Call us today at 509-928-2522 and we’ll set up an appointment.</h4>', 'Generators', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '162-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-10-27 16:07:55', '2016-10-27 16:07:55', '', 162, 'http://ceispokane.com/162-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
